PPC Falls to Lowest Since July 2005 After Saying Results Expected to Drop

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-22T07:04:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/ppc-falls-to-lowest-since-july-2005-after-saying-results-expected-to-drop.html
Pretoria Portland Cement Co., a
South African maker of the building material, fell to the lowest
intraday level since July 2005 after saying its first-half
“financial results” will fall by more than 30 percent.  The stock retreated as much as 5 percent to 24.66 rand and
traded 3.4 percent down at 25.10 rand by 9:02 a.m. in
Johannesburg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
